  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">SUSTAINING THE GAINS OF REGIONAL DRR COORDINATION HUBS</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">At the end of the project (after 5 months), the following must have been achieved:
&#x2022;	15 Hub leaders renewed/brushed up their skills and practice of CHS in emergency response, and on Safeguarding and Cash Programming; and have oriented 30 other Hub leaders on the same
&#x2022;	3 Regional and 6 Provincial Contingency Plans updated and protocols tested 
&#x2022;	3 Regional Hubs&#x2019; Emergency Response Fund set up, or activated in case emergencies occur during project implementation.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project is expected to have:  
1.	Updated the coordinating skills and practice Hub Coordinators, esp. in relation to Core Humanitarian Standards (CHS) in emergency response, with focus on Safeguarding and Cash Programming
2.	Updated the Hubs&#x2019; contingency plans and coordination protocols 
3.	Initiated the Hubs&#x2019; Emergency Response Funds through small seed grants</narrative>
  </description>
